	balance of $3,300 plus accrued interest of $1,175. The Company evaluated the application of ASC 470-50 and ASC 470-60 and concluded
	that the addition of a conversion feature constituted a debt extinguishment rather than a trouble debt restructuring. No gain or
	loss was resulted from the debt extinguishment since the fair value the new debt was the same as the old debt. See more discussion
	about the new debt in Note 4. On April 5, 2016, this note was converted in its entirety and has been surrendered to the Company.




	 






	 






